feat: social crisis simulation overhaul — algorithm engine, format system, NPC reactions, scoring reweight

Major overhaul of the social media crisis simulation to shift from
granular comment-war scoring to grand strategy evaluation.

New services: engagementAlgorithmService (per-tick reach model),
npcReactionService (persona-driven counter-posts).

Schema (migration 169): post_format, impression_pool, engagement_rate,
target_demographics, platform_removed on social_posts; demographics on
session_participants; post_engagement_log table for AAR.

Scoring: narrative_control at 40%, impression-dominance-based, strategic
ratio multiplier, pattern detection, earlier trench warfare trigger.

Post format system with 6 formats, format-specific AI grading rubrics,
format picker UI, and strategy windows (pre-authored branches).

Demographics, echo chamber content, Facebook clone UI, feed algorithm
sorting, and AAR enhancements with engagement trajectories.

Also fixes migration 167 NOW() syntax and idempotent triggers.
